<subSubSection id="E7A2B298FFE678596FEE1BAFFD7978C2" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="AF07E113FFE678596FEE1BAFFE0B79D9" blockId="19.[151,450,151,177]" box="[151,450,151,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<heading id="F44F567FFFE678596FEE1BAFFE0B79D9" bold="true" box="[151,450,151,177]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="1">
<emphasis id="9DCC3D01FFE678596FEE1BAFFE0B79D9" bold="true" box="[151,450,151,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="68B89A90FFE678596F971BAFFE0B79D9" authority="Nielson" box="[238,450,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paralidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DCC3D01FFE678596F971BAFFE9779D9" bold="true" box="[238,350,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Paralidia</emphasis>
Nielson
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF07E113FFE678596FEE1BE6FD7978C2" blockId="19.[151,1436,222,498]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Medium size, slender species, male 5.50–6.90 mm, female 7.25–8.00 mm. General color light to deep fuscous, sometimes with black markings and/or large translucent spots on forewings; head narrower than pronotum; crown very narrow, narrower than width of eyes, anterior margin produced beyond anterior margin of eyes; lateral margins carinate; pronotum and mesonotum small, length of each shorter than crown; clypeus long, narrow; male pygofer with paired caudal processes; subgenital plate always pilose; aedeagus tubular, with shaft between base and subapex always glabrous, apex with 1–3 spines.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E7A2B298FFE678596FBE1A8FFD37789A" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="AF07E113FFE678596FBE1A8FFD37789A" blockId="19.[151,1436,222,498]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="9DCC3D01FFE678596FBE1A8FFEF278A7" bold="true" box="[199,315,439,463]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus is distinguished from 
<emphasis id="9DCC3D01FFE678596DD51A8EFC8578A6" box="[684,844,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Armatoralidia</emphasis>
by the small pronotum and mesotum, and by the glabrous shaft of the aedeagus between base and subapex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
